## What to do
Create a server-side utility function that enumerates all organizations on the climateai.org PDS and fetches their info + coordinates. This replaces the Airtable index.

The function should follow the same pattern as the SDK's internal getAllAcrossOrgs (confirmed by reading SDK source at dist/index.js line 6369-6420):

```ts
import { gainforestSdk } from '@/config/gainforest-sdk.server';
import { allowedPDSDomains } from '@/config/gainforest-sdk';
import { ClimateAIAgent } from '@/lib/atproto/agent';

type IndexedOrganization = {
  did: string;
  name?: string;
  country?: string;
  lat?: number;
  lon?: number;
};

export async function listAllOrganizations(options?: {
  includeInfo?: boolean;
  includeCoordinates?: boolean;
}): Promise<IndexedOrganization[]> {
  const pdsDomain = allowedPDSDomains[0]; // 'climateai.org'

  // Step 1: List all repos on the PDS
  const agent = ClimateAIAgent; // from src/lib/atproto/agent.ts
  const reposResponse = await agent.com.atproto.sync.listRepos({ limit: 500 });
  const repos = reposResponse.data.repos;

  // Step 2: For each repo, fetch org info via SDK server caller
  const apiCaller = gainforestSdk.getServerCaller();

  const results = await Promise.all(
    repos.map(async (repo) => {
      try {
        const org: IndexedOrganization = { did: repo.did };

        if (options?.includeInfo) {
          const infoResponse = await apiCaller.gainforest.organization.info.get({
            did: repo.did,
            pdsDomain,
          });
          const info = infoResponse.value;
          // Filter: only include Public orgs
          if (info.visibility !== 'Public') return null;
          org.name = info.displayName;
          org.country = info.country;
        }

        if (options?.includeCoordinates) {
          try {
            const defaultLocation = await apiCaller.hypercerts.location.getDefault({
              did: repo.did,
              pdsDomain,
            });
            // The default location record contains an AT-URI to a certified location
            // We need to resolve it to get lat/lon
            // Check the SDK's location.getDefault response shape
            // Then fetch the actual location record for coordinates
            const locationUri = defaultLocation.value?.site; // AT-URI string
            if (locationUri) {
              // Parse the AT-URI to get rkey
              // Fetch the certified location record
              const allLocations = await apiCaller.hypercerts.location.getAll({
                did: repo.did,
                pdsDomain,
              });
              // Find the default one and extract lat/lon from the GeoJSON
              // The certified location has a 'location' field with GeoJSON
              // Use computePolygonMetrics or parse the point directly
            }
          } catch {
            // No default location — skip coordinates
          }
        }

        return org;
      } catch {
        // Repo has no org info record (test accounts, etc.) — skip
        return null;
      }
    })
  );

  return results.filter((r): r is IndexedOrganization => r !== null);
}
```

IMPORTANT: The pseudocode above is a guide — you need to adapt based on the actual SDK response shapes. Key things to figure out:
1. What does apiCaller.hypercerts.location.getDefault return? It fetches 'app.gainforest.organization.defaultSite' which contains an AT-URI to a site. Check the existing /api/list-organizations/route.ts for how it currently resolves defaultSite -> site -> lat/lon.
2. The certified location record has a 'location' field that is GeoJSON. For point locations, parse lat/lon directly. For polygon locations, compute the centroid.
3. Handle pagination: listRepos has a limit of 500 which is enough for 98 repos, but add cursor-based pagination for future growth.

Also look at how the EXISTING /api/list-organizations/route.ts fetches coordinates — it does: getRecord(defaultSite) -> parse AT-URI -> getRecord(site) -> extract lat/lon. Replicate this logic but using the SDK caller instead of raw agent calls.

